Tadpole . A stage 29 tadpole was used for the description (
Fig. 2
). Total length 19.0 mm, body length 7.6 mm , body width 5.5 mm . Snout rounded when viewed from above; body ovoid in dorsal view. Eyes black, dorsal, angled laterally, pupils white in preservative. Nares not forming tube, situated half-way between eye and tip of snout, directed dorsolaterally. Spiracle sinistral; vent dextral. Tail 3.4 mm in depth measured halfway along length; ventral tail fin begins at tail base, dorsal tail fin begins just posterior to plane of vent opening, ventral and dorsal fins relatively uniform in thickness throughout tail, tapering towards tip. Musculature depth uniform throughout, tapering towards tip, musculature depth 2.0 mm.
